<br>
It depends on how you want to look at it. We get mana savings and mana regen through SCM, MC, and something like Reinforcement "saves" by prolonging buff duration (less casting during an xp group, for example). Also add in Healing Adept -- 10% max -- and to a lesser extent Gift. <br>
<br>
Mana saved is mana earned, especially for long fights. <br>
<br>
Now...that's in addition to our own spells. But unlike wizards, we have no "familiar" that grants us mana/resists although it's been suggested more than a few times to VI that our 55 Behest spell be changed to summon a bear familiar that could add some resists and mana regen. It's not a terrible idea if you think about it since Form of the Howler is outdoor-only and 55-59/60 druids haven't got POTG/C and so forth yet. Plus Spirit of Oak is outdoor-only and wouldn't you know -- you can't use it in some zones (and doesn't stack with Glades). <br>
<br>
<br>
<i>Makes sense to me that we would. I mean somewhere it has to be registered exactly how much mana we have like our hp total. Take 10% of that total then add it on top....sigh</i> <br>
<br>
I don't know if ShowEQ shows exact numbers; I don't use it. But others here and at Graffe's (testing the various AA skills) have reported that ShowEQ is accurate more than Magelo, which lowballs the total mana by 100 or more. You could use Magelo's to set up your profile then add 100 to your total, or try some in-game tests like the one Scirocco used to determine your mana pool. I myself used POTG in-game to see how off my Magelo was, and it was quite wrong to my surprise. <br>
